On December 3rd 1972, this young couple that I’ve had the pleasure to call mom and dad.  Walked down the aisle to pledge their love for each other.  Today we celebrate their 50th wedding anniversary with family , friends and loved ones.  Mom at 20 and Dad at 26, and me at 10 months old immigrated to a new country, not speaking a word of English , with very little money in their pocket.  They came with the motivation to work hard to give me a better life and opportunity.  Through all their struggles and there were lots, there love for each other never wavered.  There love of family was always number 1.  There whole life till this very day, all they care about is if we are ok.  They have been so selfless.  I have told them many times in the last few years, mom I don’t need your money.  Go live your life with dad.  Travel , see the world.  It’s that old school immigrant parent mindset.  You work so hard to then leave everything for your kids.  They have been my inspiration and motivation.  My sister and I thank them for all the love they have given us throughout their journey.  We have been very blessed! Even through our struggles we always had love. Today is a huge milestone, a milestone not a lot of people get to celebrate anymore .  Lots of love mom and dad !  Today is your day!

Today I close the 2022 chapter of my journey.  Not going to lie , 2022 kicked my ass. Owning your own business and becoming successful at it is not always roses.  Even after so many years of doing this, you will have moments , years of adversity, ups and downs .  This year was that year for me.  The year started off with me being sued by one of the largest Jewellery brands in the world.  At first when I got served , I was excited as shit!  I said to myself, man you just made it in this industry.  After taking a step back I reminded myself this was going to cost me a lot of money.  They tried to flex their muscles on a “little guy” . What they didn’t expect was for the “little guy” to hire one of the top law firms in Silicon Valley.  My lawyers and I worked hard on a settlement that was more beneficial to me than them.  A few months later our factory facility was robbed in a high level , well organized heist.  A heist so high level you would think it came straight out of a movie.  That rocked my whole world.  At that moment all I can think of was everything I worked so hard for is now gone.  We took a major hit.  So many of our clients were affected.  The hardest thing we had to do as a business was contacting all the people that were affected to let them know their personal items were gone.  I was not expecting their reactions.  All of them showed so much empathy to the situation, symptomatic to my feelings. They were so amazing and THEY really helped me get through this.  I didn’t wait for insurance to kick in , I covered everything personally.  I wanted to make sure I replaced everything that was stolen quickly and professionally. Learn about the different shape of diamonds : 
Elongated Cushion Cut : becoming the more popular of the cushion family.  The length to width ratio creates perception of size . Good reflection and refraction of light .  Least expensive shape to buy, good value. 

Emerald Cut:  the purest of diamonds . A step cut makes it see through , very clear.  Need to go with a higher clarity of diamond.  Great length to width ratio to create size.  Not made to sparkle.  Price is in the middle in terms of shape. 

Oval Cut : most popular shape.  Great length to width ratio to create perception of size .  Outside of the round cut, it’s the best next shape to sparkle.  Great value for your money.  Middle of the pack in terms of cost. 

Round Cut : the shape that sparkles the most.  In terms of how it’s cut it will reflect and refract light the best.  The most classic shape.  The shape that holds its value the best.  Most expensive shape.  Not the largest in terms of shapes.  You gain sparkle but lose size. 

Princess Cut :  not as popular as it use to be .  One of the smallest shapes of diamonds.  Great value for your money, just above the cushion as the least expensive shape.  Sparkle is mid to low on the scale in terms of how shapes sparkle.

Radiant Cut :  same shape as an Emerald Cut, just cut to sparkle.  Also gives you great sparkle.  Great length to width to create perception of size.  Because the radiant is faceted to sparkle you can afford to go a bit lower in clarity.  A bit more expensive then the emerald. 

Which shape is your favorite?

Lab diamonds, natural diamonds, and moissanites are all types of gemstones that are used in jewelry. Here are the key differences between them:
1. Origins:
* Natural diamonds are formed deep within the earth’s crust over millions of years.
* Lab diamonds, are created in a laboratory using advanced technology that simulates the conditions under which natural diamonds are formed.
* Moissanites are naturally occurring minerals that are very rare, but are also synthesized in the lab to be used as gemstones.
2. Composition:
* Natural diamonds are made of pure carbon that has been compressed under intense heat and pressure.
* Lab diamonds have the same chemical and physical properties as natural diamonds because they are made of the same material.
* Moissanites are made of silicon carbide and have different physical and optical properties than diamonds.
3. Cost:
* Natural diamonds are generally the most expensive option, as they are rare and require significant resources to mine and process.
* Lab diamonds are generally less expensive than natural diamonds because they can be produced at a lower cost in a controlled environment.
* Moissanites are usually the least expensive option, as they are easier to produce than both natural and lab diamonds.
4. Appearance:
* Natural diamonds, lab diamonds, and moissanites can all be cut and polished to produce a brilliant, sparkling gemstone. However, there are some differences in their appearance.
* Natural diamonds and lab diamonds have a similar appearance because they are made of the same material. However, lab diamonds may have fewer inclusions or imperfections than natural diamonds because they are created in a controlled environment.
* Moissanites have a different appearance than diamonds because they have a higher refractive index and dispersion, which gives them more fire and brilliance.
Overall, the choice between lab diamonds, natural diamonds, and moissanites will depend on your personal preferences and budget. If you are looking for a more affordable option with similar qualities to a natural diamond, lab diamonds or moissanites may be a good choice.

The sparkle of a diamond is due to its unique optical properties, which are a result of its high refractive index and its ability to reflect light. When light enters a diamond, it is refracted or bent, causing the light to slow down and change direction. This bending of the light creates what is known as "internal reflection."
In addition to this internal reflection, a diamond's cut also plays a crucial role in its sparkle. The way that a diamond is cut determines how the light entering the diamond is reflected and refracted. A well-cut diamond will reflect light back to the observer's eye, creating a brilliant, sparkling appearance.
Diamonds that are cut too deep or too shallow will not reflect light as well, and will therefore not sparkle as much. The quality of the diamond's cut is determined by several factors, including the angles and proportions of the diamond's facets, the symmetry of the diamond's shape, and the quality of the diamond's polish.

Diamond clarity refers to the presence or absence of internal and external characteristics, or inclusions and blemishes, in a diamond. These characteristics can affect the diamond's beauty and value, as they can interfere with the passage of light through the stone, causing it to appear less brilliant and less transparent.

The Gemological Institute of America (GIA) is the most widely recognized organization for diamond grading and utilizes a standard scale to grade the clarity of a diamond, ranging from "Flawless" (FL) to "Included" (I3). The GIA clarity scale is based on the size, number, location, and visibility of inclusions and blemishes under 10x magnification.

Flawless (FL): These diamonds are completely free of inclusions or blemishes when viewed under 10x magnification.
Internally Flawless (IF): These diamonds have no visible inclusions under 10x magnification, but may have minor blemishes.
Very, Very Slightly Included (VVS1/VVS2): These diamonds have inclusions that are extremely difficult to see under 10x magnification, with VVS1 being slightly better clarity than VVS2.
Very Slightly Included (VS1/VS2): These diamonds have inclusions that are somewhat difficult to see under 10x magnification, with VS1 being slightly better clarity than VS2.
Slightly Included (SI1/SI2): These diamonds have inclusions that are easily visible under 10x magnification, with SI1 inclusions being slightly easier to see than SI2.
Included (I1, I2, I3): These diamonds have inclusions that are visible to the naked eye, and may affect the diamond's transparency, brilliance, and durability. I1 diamonds have the fewest and smallest inclusions, while I3 diamonds have the most and largest inclusions.

In the 19th century, diamonds became more widely available, and the tradition of giving diamond engagement rings began to take hold. In 1886, the jewelry company Tiffany & Co. introduced the "Tiffany setting," which elevated the diamond above the band and allowed it to catch more light, making it appear more brilliant.

The tradition of giving engagement rings has continued to evolve over time, with different styles and trends coming and going. Choosing a marquise diamond engagement ring offers several unique advantages that may appeal to you:

1. Distinctive Shape: The marquise cut is known for its elongated shape with pointed ends, resembling a boat or football. This shape sets it apart from traditional round or princess-cut diamonds, making it a distinctive and eye-catching choice. If you desire a ring that stands out and makes a statement, the marquise cut is an excellent option.

2. Illusion of Larger Size: The elongated shape of a marquise diamond creates an illusion of a larger size compared to other diamond shapes of the same carat weight. This means you can get a visually impressive diamond without necessarily having to invest in a higher carat weight, making it a cost-effective choice.

3. Flattering and Lengthening Effect: The elongated shape of a marquise diamond can have a flattering effect on the wearer's finger. It creates an illusion of longer and slender fingers, making it an ideal choice for those who want to enhance the appearance of their hands.

4. Unique and Vintage Appeal: Marquise-cut diamonds have a rich history and are often associated with vintage and antique jewelry. If you appreciate the charm and uniqueness of vintage-inspired designs, a marquise diamond engagement ring can be a perfect choice to capture that timeless elegance.

5. Versatile Design Options: The elongated shape of a marquise diamond allows for various design possibilities. It can be set horizontally or vertically, and you can choose from a range of settings, such as solitaire, halo, or side stone settings. This versatility allows you to customize the ring to your personal style and preferences.

Ultimately, choosing a marquise diamond engagement ring is a matter of personal taste and style. If you are drawn to its distinctive shape, desire a visually impressive diamond, and appreciate its vintage appeal, a marquise diamond engagement ring may be the perfect choice for you.

The benefits of a flat bottom ring versus a round one can vary depending on personal preference and style. 

Here are a few advantages of each:
Benefits of a flat bottom ring:

Comfort: Flat bottom rings tend to sit more comfortably on the finger compared to round rings.
The flat surface distributes the weight of the ring more evenly, reducing the chances of it spinning or sliding around on the finger.

���Stability: The flat bottom of the ring provides a stable base, making it less likely to tilt or rotate on the finger. This can be particularly beneficial for those who lead an active lifestyle or work with their hands.

���Unique design: Flat bottom rings offer a distinctive and modern look. The flat surface can be customized with engravings, patterns, or gemstone accents, allowing for a personalized and unique design.

Benefits of a round ring:

���Versatility: Round rings are versatile and can complement a wide range of styles and settings. They can be paired with various types of gemstones, settings, and metal choices, making them suitable for different tastes and preferences.
